map made by me

Welcome to Surf_Time_Limit!!

First off, I guess I should explain why it's named Surf_Time_Limit. I was really bored around 1 o'clock in the morning a few weeks back, and I decided to give myself a set amount of time to make a map. For some odd reason, I decided three hours should be a half decent amount of time to create something well, half decent. I decided to split it into 1 hour for build/textures, optimization, and design.

The map itself is pretty straight forward. It is a bit of a get a gun and kill people surf, and it is actually a lot of fun. Yes, for all of you who complain, there is a jail, although there really isn't much of a point to it, but it compliments the map quite nicely.

**********************************************

Final Changes/Additions/Fixes:
-No more spawn jumping/killing
-The first ramp turn around to Awp's is no longer possible
-Re-texture
-Additional entrances to jail/decreased camping
-A friend on UAkron suggested knives only in Jail. Now all weapons are stripped on entry to jail and you are left with a knife. (Makes it easier for the people on top of jail.)
- Took the doors off of the frames. (Another suggestion from UAkron) Now you can just walk through the portals to your destination
-Took out pieces of the awfully cluttered spiral ramps. It's now a bit more difficult to surf.
-Every player is equipped with a P228 and full Kevlar and helmet at the beginning of every round.
- Optimization changes
-Increased some of the sizes of the water pools

(There have been a lot of changes to this map to make it the best it could be with the design that I originally used. Many will agree with me when I say that the original design could have been more thought out, so I see no point in working on this any further. These changes should increase the popularity of the map, and the enjoyment of the surf.)

All questions/complaints/comments/advice/opinions:

Xfire: Wowyourgaiy
Email: Phantomoper3@comcast.net

Gentlemen, I give you surf_timewarp, a new tier 6, 5 staged map.

It took me upwards from 8 months to finish this, and most agree it was worth the wait. The map has a general theme, you travel through time attempting to assassinate an evil emperor. Pretty generic as far as stories go but hey, I tried. Stages each have tangible themes: stage 1 is ancient egypt, stage 2 is medieval times, stage 3 is the 1800's, stage 4 is the emperor's palace, and stage 5 is the time machine.

Don't be surprised if you get frustrated, it's a tough map. But a lot of people seem to appreciate that nowadays. It has no jail, but that's because I don't really care enough to make one.

Surf_the_gloaming, by Roosta

After an extended leave of absence from the surf mapping community due to intense school work, I am finally back and mapping. I begin my return with this map: surf_the_gloaming (pronounced "the glow-ming").

This map all begins with FAJ (what good maps isn't he a part of?). He told me to get off my lazy ass and make an "EPIC" surf map. After much enticing, I finally got around to doing it. This is the result. I am not so sure how epic this map is; I leave that to you to decide. I incorporated all aspects of mapping in which I am proficient: skyboxes, ramps, neat geometry, flow, learning curves, texturing, and logic systems. This map has taught me much.

It's just a linear surf map. Nothing more, nothing less (well, maybe a little bit more). There are a few secrets, some of which I particularly enjoy (Scout Battles!)

At spawn it is IMPOSSIBLE to hit an enemy through the nearly invisible wall. Incase it looks weird to you, you are pushed very quickly down the first ramps when you don't expect it which makes it impossible to spawn attack/kill/hop. You fly down the first series of ramps, then you have to land on one of the green rectangles, then you have to do a long surf, curl up to a higher ramp and out a little hole. This then takes you to a falling room which is impossible to do if you don't just jump over all the boxes =)

Then you get to the top of jail with LOADS of guns and he grenades, and you can go back to the other rooms to hunt people.

There is a slow spawn pusher which pushes AFKzors so they don't just be stuck there and use up all the round time!

****Recommended CVars:****

**sv_airaccelerate 1000**

No other files are required, just the map.

Surf_teenpregnancy_lite update:
An improved version is here! Better lighting. The front reservoir will break after 60 seconds, allowing for less experienced players to surf. The small tear will still be available with access to a knife for players who would like to have weapons while they surf. There will be a single knife at the egg (end of map) to be able to destroy the breakable walls. Failing on any level will bring you back to the beginning of that particular level, the only exception is level 2, floor 1.

surf_teenpregnancy_v1 update:
Fixed global jail teleport issues.

Surf_teenpregnancy, for all the kids who slept through 8th grade health class.

Why take a life when you can create one? This anatomically semi-correct representation of our favorite subject is now brought to new light in the form of a killer surf map. Three levels, three secrets, and one extremely creative jail makes for an intense, if not freakin' hilarious experience!

Tips: 1. Certain parts of the map are difficult, keep practicing. This is especially true in the beginning. The opening is small but very doable. 2. The "dome" has glass doors that break 3. The doctor's utensil's control system is inverted. Use the back key to move the object forward, and the forward key to move the object backwards. 4. The secret room is on the end of the second level to the left, where there seems to be a shadow platform. Bunnyhop it to the corner. Remember to use that well-earned grenade wisely.

Map by: Butterknife (aka Jaekto)
Jail layout idea based on ny_superhappiest
Special thanks to all the testers and brainstormers at intoxgaming

This map took a while to make but it's finally done!

surf_technique is a Tier 5 map with 7 Stages and 5 Bonuses.

The map is focused on gameplay oriented around using as few ramps as possible per stage but exploring one concept per stage. It relies heavily on surfing each ramp as well as possible.

The bonuses range from moderately easy to incredibly hard. I hope people have a fun challenge trying to complete them all!

Big thanks to not_a_zombie for helping out and testing a ton for a very long time. Also big thanks to beetle179 for testing and helping tweak red bonus to be very hard, as well as making my map more public via his stream.

<center> * Surf_Syria_again * 

Well, here it is *cough* again *cough*

I decided to finally redo my previous map "Surf__Syria" because of some bugs that I discovered.

Many of these bugs were found thanks to beta testers, and helpful surfers.

Almost every level is retextured, and made slightly harder.

The two last levels have changed order.

The two last levels are pretty hard, cause some people thought it was way too easy.

Timer decreased from 8 minutes to 4 minutes.

All bugs should be fixed, if not report to me on steam: jolas

Jail is improved in many ways.

- Optmized even more.
- Removed the possibility of people getting away from the "cutters".
- Added system to reward you 10 kill points for beating the map.
- Gave you a m249/para gun if you wish to shoot the "losers"
- Changed the pink button to ornage (lol)
- That's all. :D

Hope you enjoy & Have fun on my map.
